      "title": "South Korea presidential office rejects Coupang and US claims of discriminatory treatment",
      "summary": "Coupang 관련 기사다. 기사 제목은 'South Korea presidential office rejects Coupang and US claims of discriminatory treatment'이다. A US House Judiciary Committee report accused South Korea of discriminatory treatment of the US-listed e-commerce firm. The investigations of Coupang were conducted on a non-discriminatory basis, Wi said at a press conference called to announce Lee’s attendance at a NATO summit in Turkey Wi also disputed Coupang’s assertion that customer information was compromised and downloaded for only about 3,000 accounts in the breach ” South Korean authorities have determined that a former Coupang employee in China accessed customer records using company login credentials, and officials have been unable to determine how the information was used or where it ultimately ended up, Wi said Wi also rejected suggestions in the congressional report that Lee’s office was involved in pressuring Coupang to retrieve equipment in China linked to the breach The report alleged that South Korea’s spy agency pressured Coupang to retrieve devices in China connected to the former employee responsible for the breach, and that Lee was aware of the operation that recovered some of the equipment. 이 기사는 해당 기업과 연결된 해외 보도를 바탕으로 정리했다.",
      "original_title": "South Korea presidential office rejects Coupang and US claims of discriminatory treatment",
      "original_summary": "A US House Judiciary Committee report accused South Korea of discriminatory treatment of the US-listed e-commerce firm.",
      "company_summary": "Coupang 관련 기사다. 기사 제목은 'South Korea presidential office rejects Coupang and US claims of discriminatory treatment'이다. A US House Judiciary Committee report accused South Korea of discriminatory treatment of the US-listed e-commerce firm. The investigations of Coupang were conducted on a non-discriminatory basis, Wi said at a press conference called to announce Lee’s attendance at a NATO summit in Turkey Wi also disputed Coupang’s assertion that customer information was compromised and downloaded for only about 3,000 accounts in the breach ” South Korean authorities have determined that a former Coupang employee in China accessed customer records using company login credentials, and officials have been unable to determine how the information was used or where it ultimately ended up, Wi said Wi also rejected suggestions in the congressional report that Lee’s office was involved in pressuring Coupang to retrieve equipment in China linked to the breach The report alleged that South Korea’s spy agency pressured Coupang to retrieve devices in China connected to the former employee responsible for the breach, and that Lee was aware of the operation that recovered some of the equipment. 이 기사는 해당 기업과 연결된 해외 보도를 바탕으로 정리했다.",
